{"word":"ἐπιπολή","slug":"ἐπιπολή","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπιπολή</b></el> <el>(ἐπιπολή, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐπιπέλομαι'><el>ἐπιπέλομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a surface</i>: mostly in <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <el>ἐπιπολῆς</el> as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <i>on the surface, a-top</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>ἐπιπολῆς</el> also as <a href='S:Preposition'><a href='S:Preposition'>prep.</a></a> <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>on the top of, above</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><el>Ἐπιπολαί, αἱ</el>, an eminence near Syracuse, <i>with a flat surface</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}